quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  5,109,"ňĻConsiderňļ the Day Allah will gather the messengers and say, ‚ÄúWhat response did you receive?‚ÄĚ They will reply, ‚ÄúWe have no knowledge ňĻcompared to Youňļ! You ňĻaloneňļ are indeed the Knower of all unseen.‚ÄĚ"
  5,110,"And ňĻon Judgment Dayňļ Allah will say, ‚ÄúO Jesus, son of Mary! Remember My favour upon you and your mother: how I supported you with the holy spirit¬†so you spoke to people in ňĻyourňļ infancy and adulthood. How I taught you writing, wisdom, the Torah, and the Gospel. How you moulded a bird from clay‚ÄĒby My Will‚ÄĒand breathed into it and it became a ňĻrealňļ bird‚ÄĒby My Will. How you healed the blind and the lepers‚ÄĒby My Will. How you brought the dead to life‚ÄĒby My Will. How I prevented the Children of Israel from harming you when you came to them with clear proofs and the disbelievers among them said, ‚ÄúThis is nothing but pure magic.‚ÄĚ"
  5,111,"And how I inspired the disciples, ‚ÄúBelieve in Me and My messenger!‚ÄĚ They declared, ‚ÄúWe believe and bear witness that we fully submit ňĻto Allahňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  5,112,"ňĻRememberňļ when the disciples asked, ‚ÄúO Jesus, son of Mary! Would your Lord be willing to send down to us a table spread with food from heaven?‚ÄĚ Jesus answered, ‚ÄúFear Allah if you are ňĻtrulyňļ believers.‚ÄĚ"
  5,113,"They said, ‚ÄúWe ňĻonlyňļ wish to eat from it to reassure our hearts, to verify you are indeed truthful to us, and to become its witnesses.‚ÄĚ"
  5,114,"Jesus, son of Mary, prayed, ‚ÄúO Allah, our Lord! Send us from heaven a table spread with food as a feast for us‚ÄĒthe first and last of us‚ÄĒand as a sign from You. Provide for us! You are indeed the Best Provider.‚ÄĚ"
  5,115,"Allah answered, ‚ÄúI am sending it down to you. But whoever among you denies afterwards will be subjected to a torment I have never inflicted on anyone of My creation.‚ÄĚ"
  5,116,"And ňĻon Judgment Dayňļ Allah will say, ‚ÄúO Jesus, son of Mary! Did you ever ask the people to worship you and your mother as gods besides Allah?‚ÄĚ He will answer, ‚ÄúGlory be to You! How could I ever say what I had no right to say? If I had said such a thing, you would have certainly known it. You know what is ňĻhiddenňļ within me, but I do not know what is within You. Indeed, You ňĻaloneňļ are the Knower of all unseen"
  5,117,"I never told them anything except what You ordered me to say: ‚ÄúWorship Allah‚ÄĒmy Lord and your Lord!‚ÄĚ And I was witness over them as long as I remained among them. But when You took me,¬†You were the Witness over them‚ÄĒand You are a Witness over all things"
  5,118,"If You punish them, they belong to You after all.¬†But if You forgive them, You are surely the Almighty, All-Wise.‚ÄĚ"
  5,119,"Allah will declare, ‚ÄúThis is the Day when ňĻonlyňļ the faithful will benefit from their faithfulness. Theirs are Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. Allah is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. That is the ultimate triumph.‚ÄĚ"
  5,120,To Allah ňĻaloneňļ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and everything within. And He is Most Capable of everything
  6,1,All praise is for Allah Who created the heavens and the earth and made darkness and light.¬†Yet the disbelievers set up equals to their Lord ňĻin worshipňļ
  6,2,"He is the One Who created you from clay,¬†then appointed a term ňĻfor your deathňļ and another known only to Him ňĻfor your resurrectionňļ‚ÄĒyet you continue to doubt"
  6,3,"He is the Only True God in the heavens and the earth. He knows whatever you conceal and whatever you reveal, and knows whatever you do"
  6,4,"Whenever a sign comes to them from their Lord, they turn away from it"
  6,5,"They have indeed rejected the truth when it came to them, so they will soon face the consequences of their ridicule"
  6,6,Have they not seen how many ňĻdisbelievingňļ peoples¬†We destroyed before them? We had made them more established in the land than you. We sent down abundant rain for them and made rivers flow at their feet. Then We destroyed them for their sins and replaced them with other peoples
  6,7,"Had We sent down to you ňĻO Prophetňļ a revelation in writing and they were to touch it with their own hands, the disbelievers would still have said, ‚ÄúThis is nothing but pure magic!‚ÄĚ"
  6,8,"They say, ‚ÄúWhy has no ňĻvisibleňļ angel come with him?‚ÄĚ Had We sent down an angel, the matter would have certainly been settled ňĻat onceňļ,¬†and they would have never been given more time ňĻto repentňļ"
  6,9,"And if We had sent an angel, We would have certainly made it ňĻassume the form ofňļ a man‚ÄĒleaving them more confused than they already are"
  6,10,"ňĻOtherňļ messengers had already been ridiculed before you ňĻO Prophetňļ, but those who mocked them were overtaken by what they used to ridicule"
  6,11,"Say, ‚ÄúTravel throughout the land and see the fate of the deniers.‚ÄĚ"
  6,12,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúTo whom belongs everything in the heavens and the earth?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúTo Allah!‚ÄĚ He has taken upon Himself to be Merciful. He will certainly gather ňĻall ofňļ you together for the Day of Judgment‚ÄĒabout which there is no doubt. But those who have ruined themselves will never believe"